core.signals module

core.signals.incident_post_save(sender, instance, created, **kwargs)[source]

Signal handler for post-save operations on Incident model.

Sends a POST request to the incident callback endpoint upon creation of a new incident. Updates the status of associated alerts to ‘closed’ if the incident is acknowledged.

Parameters: - sender: Model class sending the signal. - instance: Instance of the Incident model. - created: Boolean indicating whether the instance was created. - kwargs: Additional keyword arguments.

Returns: - None
